<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-04T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-04T09:00:00-05:00" n="843" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d843">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/136</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-04T16:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>339. Foreign Minister tells me that there is no doubt about the
                                ratification of the treaty in November. Three parties have agreed to
                                support it; but it will increase the majority if the United States
                                Senate ratifies the treaty as soon as possible. This I look upon as
                                most desirable. A delay may produce other delays here.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>